      <h1>ADYNOVI<sup>&reg;</sup><span class="triangle">&#9660;</span> (rurioctocog alfa pegol) – for the treatment of <span class="orphan">haemophilia A</span> in adults and children over <span class="orphan">12 years</span> of age</h1>
      <p>Welcome to the ADYNOVI patient website.</p>
      <p>Your haemophilia treatment centre has provided you with access to this Takeda-developed website because they have prescribed ADYNOVI for you as a treatment or a preventative treatment (prophylaxis) for <span class="orphan">haemophilia A.</span></p>
      <p>ADYNOVI is an ‘extended half-life’ (or EHL) factor VIII treatment.</p>
      <p>Other treatments for haemophilia A called ‘standard half-life’ (or SHL) factor VIII, stay in the blood for a relatively shorter time compared with EHL treatments. SHL factor treatments require repeat injections for prophylaxis (every 2-3 days for <span class="orphan">haemophilia A).</span></p>
      <p>ADYNOVI contains the active substance rurioctocog alfa pegol (pegylated human coagulation factor VIII). It has been modified to prolong its duration of action. This means that ADYNOVI stays in the blood for longer than with an SHL treatment and may reduce the number of injections needed.</p>
      <p>Here you will find information about haemophilia (including symptoms and key facts), support regarding your treatment with ADYNOVI, and sources of further advice and information.</p>
